  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance for Afghan Returnee, Displaced and Otherwise Vulnerable Populations and Humanitarian Response Strengthening</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under this project, IOM is providing humanitarian post-arrival assistance to vulnerable undocumented returnees; unconditional cash assistance to returnees; and non-food items to families in the four major border crossing provinces. Additionally, IOM is ensuring the continuity of essential basic primary health care, including critical COVID-19 response measures, focusing on multiple displaced and mobile populations, as well as responding to critical water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) needs. Further, through its Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM), IOM is implementing Emergency Event Tracking (EET) across Afghanistan and flow monitoring at 10 key border crossings and transit hubs.</narrative>
  </description>
